        <abstract> 
<p>There is ‘some gradation in perfection with mammals in the mammery glands’. Discusses milk secretion in <hi rend="italic">Echidna</hi>. Instances a fish in which the ova hatch in a sack on the male and the young feed on mucus secreted by the sack lining; ‘here … we see what might be the commencement of a simple mammery gland’.</p> 
        </abstract>
